n---\n\n### Task 2: Utility Functions\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/utils.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Implement deep clone**\n\n```typescript\nexport function deepClone<T>(obj: T): T {\n  return JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(obj));\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Implement generateId**\n\n```typescript\nlet counter = 0;\nexport function generateId(): string {\n  return `v_${Date.now()}_${counter++}`;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Implement three-way merge**\n\nThree-way merge logic:\n- Takes base (common ancestor), ours (current branch), theirs (source branch)\n- Walks all keys across all three objects recursively\n- If only one side changed a field from base, take that change\n- If both changed to the same value, no conflict\n- If both changed to different values, conflict (use \"ours\" in merged result)\n- For nested objects, recurse\n- For deleted documents: if one side deleted and other didn't modify, accept deletion; if one deleted and other modified, conflict\n\n```typescript\nexport function threeWayMerge(\n  base: Record<string, any>,\n  ours: Record<string, any>,\n  theirs: Record<string, any>,\n  path: string = ''\n): { merged: Record<string, any>; conflicts: Array<{ path: string; base: any; ours: any; theirs: any }> } {\n  // Collect all keys from all three\n  const allKeys = new Set([...Object.keys(base), ...Object.keys(ours), ...Object.keys(theirs)]);\n  const merged: Record<string, any> = {};\n  const conflicts: Array<{ path: string; base: any; ours: any; theirs: any }> = [];\n\n  for (const key of allKeys) {\n    const currentPath = path ? `${path}.${key}` : key;\n    const baseVal = base[key];\n    const oursVal = ours[key];\n    const theirsVal = theirs[key];\n\n    const baseStr = JSON.stringify(baseVal);\n    const oursStr = JSON.stringify(oursVal);\n    const theirsStr = JSON.stringify(theirsVal);\n\n    const oursChanged = oursStr !== baseStr;\n    const theirsChanged = theirsStr !== baseStr;\n\n    if (!oursChanged && !theirsChanged) {\n      // No changes - keep base (if it exists)\n      if (key in base) merged[key] = deepClone(baseVal);\n      else if (key in ours) merged[key] = deepClone(oursVal);\n    } else if (oursChanged && !theirsChanged) {\n      // Only ours changed\n      if (key in ours) merged[key] = deepClone(oursVal);\n      // else: ours deleted the key\n    } else if (!oursChanged && theirsChanged) {\n      // Only theirs changed\n      if (key in theirs) merged[key] = deepClone(theirsVal);\n      // else: theirs deleted the key\n    } else {\n      // Both changed\n      if (oursStr === theirsStr) {\n        // Both changed to same value\n        if (key in ours) merged[key] = deepClone(oursVal);\n      } else if (\n        typeof oursVal === 'object' && oursVal !== null && !Array.isArray(oursVal) &&\n        typeof theirsVal === 'object' && theirsVal !== null && !Array.isArray(theirsVal) &&\n        typeof baseVal === 'object' && baseVal !== null && !Array.isArray(baseVal)\n      ) {\n        // Both are objects - recurse\n        const sub = threeWayMerge(baseVal, oursVal, theirsVal, currentPath);\n        merged[key] = sub.merged;\n        conflicts.push(...sub.conflicts);\n      } else {\n        // Conflict - use ours for merged result\n        merged[key] = deepClone(oursVal);\n        conflicts.push({ path: currentPath, base: deepClone(baseVal), ours: deepClone(oursVal), theirs: deepClone(theirsVal) });\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  return { merged, conflicts };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: DocumentStore Class\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/store.ts`\n\nCore implementation:\n- `branches: Map<string, BranchData>` — stores all branch data\n- `currentBranch: string` — tracks active branch (default \"main\")\n- CRUD operations work against `this.branches.get(this.currentBranch).documents`\n- `createBranch` snapshots the source branch documents (deep clone)\n- `merge` performs three-way merge using the parent snapshot as common ancestor\n\nKey behaviors:\n- All content stored/retrieved via deepClone to prevent mutation\n- Version IDs are unique strings\n- Timestamps use Date.now()\n- Deleted documents throw on get/update/delete\n- History returns chronological order (oldest first, which is natural push order)\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Entry Point\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/index.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport { DocumentStore } from './store.js';\nexport type { Version, MergeResult, Conflict } from './types.js';\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Tests\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `tests/store.test.ts`\n\nTest categories:\n1. CRUD basics (create, get, update, delete, throws)\n2. Deep clone isolation (mutating returned objects doesn't affect store)\n3. Version history (create + updates generate versions, chronological order)\n4. getVersion retrieval\n5. Branching (create branch, switch, isolation between branches)\n6. Branch from specific branch\n7. Simple merge (only one side changed)\n8. Three-way merge (both sides changed different fields)\n9. Merge conflicts (both sides changed same field differently)\n10. Merge with no conflicts auto-applies\n11. Merge with conflicts does not apply\n12. Merge with document created on one branch\n13. Merge with document deleted on one branch\n14. Multiple documents merge independently\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Build, Lint, Verify\n\nRun: `npm run build && npm run lint && npm test`\n\nFix any issues that arise.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
